The paper discusses the use of neural networks to generate adversarial attacks and formulate a game-theoretic framework for attacker-defender interaction. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with the security aspect of machine learning models, indicating that it could also belong to the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
